body:
puh... I just stumbled on the same issue with my new client, when trying to migrate to play 2.6
They also use the "Link" header to indicate which urls are "prev", "next" and "self".. the client also expects the quotes to be there. 

I'm not sure on how to use the workaround with `RawHeader` as I'm in a Play-Action and the only methods for headers only takes Strings or a Date.. 

Sample code looks like this
```
  def fakeApplication: Application = {
    val app = new GuiceApplicationBuilder()
      .routes {
        case ("GET" | "HEAD", url) if List("/stock/changes/latest", "/stock/changes/100").contains(url) => Action {
          Ok(writeParts("--boundary", Seq((dateFive, "100-1"), (dateFive, "100-0")), provideContentId = provideContentId))
            .withHeaders("Link" -> "</stock/changes/090>; rel=\"prev\", </stock/changes/100>; rel=\"self\"")
            .withHeaders(HeaderNames.CACHE_CONTROL -> "no-cache")
            .withHeaders(HeaderNames.LAST_MODIFIED -> DateUtil.formatDate(dateFive))
            .as("multipart/package; boundary=\"boundary\"")
        }
   .build()
}
  val LinkPattern = "<(.*)>.*rel=\"(.*)\"".r

  "SomeConsumer" should {
    "[>>] determine start url (earliest modification) without faults" in new WithServer(fakeApplication, port) {
      private val consumer = createFeedConsumer()
      consumer.determineStartUrl(host, path, base.minusDays(14).getMillis) await() must beSome("/stock/changes/060") // this basically connects to the local application and retrieves the response, expecting the Link header to be formatted like the linkPattern above
      ok
    }
}
```

@jroper and @gavares,

There is a fix for this issue on [Play 2.6.13](https://discuss.lightbend.com/t/play-2-6-13-released/629). Could you please try this new version and confirm it is working for you guys?

Thanks!
